The Nigeria Police Force (NPF),  Cross River  Command has confirmed the kidnap of the state Chairman of Nigeria Labour Congress, Ben Ukpepi at his residence in Akpabuyo local government area of the state. The State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Irene Ugbo, disclosed this in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria on Wednesday in Calabar. Ugbo said that the NLC Chairman was kidnapped at about 7.30pm on Tuesday night by suspected kidnappers. “The story of the kidnap of the NLC Chairman is true. He was kidnapped in Akpabuyo in his house. “We got the report this morning. The Anti Cultism and Kidnapping Unit are on top of the situation to rescue him,” she said. 